  "text": "Hybrid or heterogeneous systems integrated advantages of multiple solutions and have been widely used in realtime vision applications in recent years. In general, CPU-GPU is the most popular hybrid solution in the field of computer vision for its excellent performance. [CITATION_1] However, most CPU-GPU heterogeneous systems are fabricated as computers or workstations, which have high power consumption and are not suitable for small-scale mobile robots. Moreover, programs of vision algorithm shall be carefully optimized to use CPU and GPU simultaneously for a high utilization rate. Besides, the program portability problem between some types of NVIDIA GPUs still exists.",
